<p><a name="Criticisms" id="Criticisms"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Digital_gold_currency&amp;action=edit&amp;section=13" title="Edit section: Criticisms">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Criticisms</span></h2>
<p>DGC providers and exchangers have been accused of being a medium for fraudulent <a href="/wiki/High-yield_investment_program" title="High-yield investment program">high-yield investment program</a> (HYIP) schemes. In January 2006, <i><a href="/wiki/BusinessWeek" title="BusinessWeek">BusinessWeek</a></i> reported that <a href="/wiki/ShadowCrew" title="ShadowCrew">ShadowCrew</a>, an online gang, used the <a href="/wiki/E-gold" title="E-gold">e-gold</a> system in a massive <a href="/wiki/Identity_theft" title="Identity theft">identity theft</a> and fraud scheme.<sup id="cite_ref-12" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-12" title=""><span>[</span>13<span>]</span></a></sup> Traditional banks are also used frequently for such fraud. Allegations that e-gold is a safe medium for crime and fraud are strongly denied by its Chairman and founder, Dr. <a href="/wiki/Douglas_Jackson_(businessman)" title="Douglas Jackson (businessman)">Douglas Jackson</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-13" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-13" title=""><span>[</span>14<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<p>Many DGC providers do not disclose the amount of bullion stored (see table), or do not allow independent external bullion audits, raising concerns that such companies do not maintain a 100% <a href="/wiki/Reserve_ratio" title="Reserve ratio" class="mw-redirect">reserve ratio</a>, or that their currency is entirely virtual and not backed by physical gold at all.</p>
<p><a name="Cultural_references" id="Cultural_references"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Digital_gold_currency&amp;action=edit&amp;section=14" title="Edit section: Cultural references">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Cultural references</span></h2>
<ul>
<li>The novel <a href="/wiki/Cryptonomicon" title="Cryptonomicon">Cryptonomicon</a> by <a href="/wiki/Neal_Stephenson" title="Neal Stephenson">Neal Stephenson</a> uses the idea of a gold-based digital currency in combination with strong <a href="/wiki/Cryptography" title="Cryptography">cryptography</a>.</li>
</ul>
